
[1]shop

   SHOP, n.

   1. A builking in which goods, wares, drugs, &c. are sold by retail.

   2. a building in which mechanics work, and where they keep their
   manufactures for sale.

   Keep your shop, and your shop will keep you. Franklin.

   SHOP, v.i. To visit shops for purchasing goods; used chiefly in the
   participle; as, the laky is shopping.
